FT  31 JUL 92 / World Stock Markets: South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
JOHANNESBURG closed off earlier highs ahead of President FW De Klerk's state
of the nation address. The overall index gained 17 to 3,433 while
industrials were up 31 at 4,230. Golds fell to close 17 lower at 1,077.
