FT  31 JUL 92 / Observer: Dying fall
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
For all his knowledge about original sin, Bishop Michael Marshall has been
snared by a sin whose origins he wot not of. As a result, he has arrived
home from running an Anglican mission in the US without his treasured piano.
On applying to Washington for an export licence for the instrument, he was
told that since it had ivory keys, he must specify where the sin of killing
the elephant they came from had been committed.
As he didn't know, the licence was refused. And when his secretary
protested, the bureaucracy's only reply was: 'The bishop should not have
bought a piano with ivory keys.'
