<HEADLINE>
FT  31 JUL 92 / BCCI liquidators to contact creditors
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LIQUIDATORS to the collapsed Bank of Credit and Commerce International will
circulate a letter to creditors in the next two weeks on behalf of the
Luxembourg court giving recommendations for dividing the bank's assets.
Mr Brian Smouha, of accountants Touche Ross, and Mr Georges Baden and Mr
Julien Roden, who were appointed joint liquidators to BCCI SA by the
Luxembourg court, are expected to continue pressing for their liquidation
package, which offers creditors up to Dollars 1.7bn.
They will write to about 50,000 creditors and place newspaper advertisements
laying out the arguments.
The letter was requested in an order issued by the court last week, when it
postponed a decision on whether to approve the deal until October 7, to hear
creditors' views.
Some creditors have attempted to challenge the deal, calling for larger
contributions from the government of Abu Dhabi, the majority shareholders in
the bank, or for litigation to recover more assets.
The liquidators say the government of Abu Dhabi will not contribute any more
money, and that litigation would delay any dividend to creditors for many
years.
</TEXT>
