aim to win business in these republics.
The deal provides Turkish exporters with 100 per cent trade insurance cover,
Dollars 200m for Kazakhstan and the rest for Kyrgyzstan. A list of export
items has still to be agreed. The accord follows a Dollars 1.7bn power plant
deal in Kazakhstan earlier this month.
