<TEXT>
THE Finnish trade and industry minister, Mr Kauko Juhantalo, asked by his
Centre Party to stand down after reports he was being sued for debt, sent an
open letter of resignation to President Mauno Koivisto yesterday, Reuter
reports from Helsinki.
'I hereby respectfully request I be relieved of membership in the cabinet,'
