PAKISTAN AND Algeria are to buy Dollars 150m worth of Malaysian palm oil
under the Malaysian government's recently inaugurated long term export
credit financing programme.
Mr Lim Keng Yaik, the Malaysian Primary Industries Minister, said contracts
giving Pakistan a Dollars 100m credit facility and Algeria one of Dollars
