Malaysia's export credit financing programme for palm oil extends a total of
Dollars 500m to six countries - China, India, Egypt, the Commonwealth of
Independent States, Pakistan and Algeria.
Mr Lim said credits would be granted for up to two years as part of the
government's strategy to secure big, long term palm oil contracts. 'The
contracts will ensure a ready market for the commodity in the years to
come,' he added.
