FT  30 JUL 92 / Councils meet housing standards
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
LOCAL authorities are meeting obligations imposed by the Citizen's Charter
in the maintenance of their housing stock, but need to include tenants more
in housing management processes, according to the Audit Commission, the
local government watchdog.
In a report on housing services, the commission says 95 per cent of urgent
repairs were carried out within target times - often as little as a few
hours - set by the councils surveyed. Most tenants were offered choices when
significant work was carried out on their homes.
Tenants were represented on estate management bodies in only 13 per cent of
the district councils surveyed.
