STRONG JUNE sales were behind a small improvement in second-quarter profits
at Eastman Kodak, the US photographic products group, agencies report from
Rochester.
Net income amounted to Dollars 361m or Dollars 1.11 a share, against Dollars
357m or Dollars 1.10 in the same period last year.
This brought net income for the first half to Dollars 506m or Dollars 1.56 a
share, against Dollars 535m or Dollars 1.65 a year earlier.
Fully diluted earnings per share were Dollars 1.51 against Dollars 1.64 for
the half-year and Dollars 1.06 against Dollars 1.09 for the latest quarter.
First-half sales totalled Dollars 975bn against Dollars 9.52bn last year
with the second quarter generating Dollars 5.27bn, compared with Dollars
5.03bn the same period a year earlier.
Mr Kay Whitmore, chairman, said: 'The results we delivered for the first
half were consistent with our 1992 operating plan and this gives us
confidence that the year as a whole will deliver what we expect: moderately
higher sales and good gains in earnings,'.
