FT  29 JUL 92 / The Barcelona Olympics: Judo silver for Britain
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Ray Stevens was the toast of the British Olympic team in Barcelona after
finally ending their medal famine with a judo silver. The 29-year-old
fitness coach from South London was just one fight away from becoming the
first British judo player ever to win Olympic gold, but had to concede the
gold in the light-heavyweight final to Hungarian Antal Kovacs.
Theo Meijer of the Netherlands and Dmitri Sergeev of the Unified Team won
the bronze medals.
Kim Mi-Jung of South Korea won the women's half-heavyweight (72kg) class
judo gold meda, beating Yoko Tanabe of Japan.
